==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rodomont
<hw>Rod"o*mont</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>rodomont</ets>, It. <ets>rodomonte</ets>, fr. <ets>Rodomonte</ets>,
<ets>Rodamonte</ets>, a boasting hero in the ⟦ldquo⟧Orlando
Furioso⟦rdquo⟧ of Ariosto, and the ⟦ldquo⟧Orlando Innamorato⟦rdquo⟧ of
Bojardo; properly, one who rolls away mountains; Prov. It.
<ets>rodare</ets> to roll away (fr. L. <ets>rota</ets> a wheel) + It.
<ets>monte</ets> a mountain, L. <ets>mons</ets>. See <er>Rotary</er>,
<er>Mount</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>A vain or blustering boaster;
a braggart; a braggadocio.</def> <rj><au>Sir T. Herbert.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rodomont</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Rodomont
<hw>Rod"o*mont</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Bragging; vainly
boasting.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rodomontade</ent>⟦br⟧
